org.apache.flink.api.java.functions

接口 KeySelector<IN,KEY>

  • 类型参数:
    IN - Type of objects to extract the key from.
    KEY - Type of key.
    所有超级接口:
    Function, java.io.Serializable
    所有已知实现类:
    CoGroupedStreams.UnionKeySelector, GroupedProcessingTimeWindowExample.FirstFieldKeyExtractor, KeySelectorUtil.ArrayKeySelector, KeySelectorUtil.ComparableKeySelector, KeySelectorUtil.OneKeySelector, NullByteKeySelector, WindowJoin.NameKeySelector

    @Public
public interface KeySelector<IN,KEY>
extends Function, java.io.Serializable
    The KeySelector allows to use deterministic objects for operations such as reduce, reduceGroup, join, coGoup, etc. If invoked multiple times on the same object, the returned key must be the same. The extractor takes an object and returns the deterministic key for that object.

    • 方法概要

      所有方法 实例方法 抽象方法 
      限定符和类型 方法和说明
      KEY getKey(IN value)
      User-defined function that deterministically extracts the key from an object.

    • 方法详细资料

      • getKey

        KEY getKey(IN value)
    throws java.lang.Exception
        User-defined function that deterministically extracts the key from an object. For example for a class: 
                public class Word {
                String word;
                int count;
        }
        The key extractor could return the word as a key to group all Word objects by the String they contain. The code would look like this 
                public String getKey(Word w) {
                return w.word;
        }
        参数:
        value - The object to get the key from.
        返回:
        The extracted key.
        抛出:
        java.lang.Exception - Throwing an exception will cause the execution of the respective task to fail, and trigger recovery or cancellation of the program.
